line_1: CUPID ne'er shall make me languish,
line_2: Lovers' sighs, and tears, and anguish,

line_1: When wearisome sickness has taught me to languish
line_2: Let me hope (ah! how soon would it lessen my anguish),

line_1: Our cheerful hours without thee languish: '
line_2: All! hush! .... nor wake a parent's anguish!

line_1: 'Midst beauty and pleasure's gay triumphs, to languish
line_2: And droop without knowing the source of my anguish;

line_1: Sent in this foul clime to languish,

line_2: Who can speak a mother's anguish,

line_1: How do your tuneful Echo's languish,
line_2: Mute, but to the voice of Anguish!

line_1: How do your tuneful echoes languish,
line_2: Mute, but to the voice of anguish?

line_1: I hail thee now, no longer vainly languish,
line_2: The tedious hours I told With Watchful anguish,

line_1: Leave me then alone to languish;
line_2: Think not time can heal my anguish;
